    <detaileddescription>
<para>Extension: Detect whether given execution policy makes algorithms asynchronous</para><para><orderedlist>
<listitem><para>The type <ref refid="structhpx_1_1parallel_1_1execution_1_1is__async__execution__policy" kindref="compound">is_async_execution_policy</ref> can be used to detect asynchronous execution policies for the purpose of excluding function signatures from otherwise ambiguous overload resolution participation.</para></listitem><listitem><para>If T is the type of a standard or implementation-defined execution policy, is_async_execution_policy&lt;T&gt; shall be publicly derived from integral_constant&lt;bool, true&gt;, otherwise from integral_constant&lt;bool, false&gt;.</para></listitem><listitem><para>The behavior of a program that adds specializations for <ref refid="structhpx_1_1parallel_1_1execution_1_1is__async__execution__policy" kindref="compound">is_async_execution_policy</ref> is undefined. </para></listitem></orderedlist>
</para>    </detaileddescription>
